featured_question.answer: Nice question. But there are no government approved transport services to Hajo Poa Mecca. Not only in Mecca, there are no transportation services available to the temples too. Why the government didn't give that I don't know. But you can get auto-rickshaws to go to mecca from hajo. N the rate is so reasonable. Maybe that's why govt didn't provide any transportation service as it is cheaper already.

The natural beauty of Poa Mecca, Assam Hajo is truly remarkable, and it's worth visiting for anyone looking to escape the hustle and bustle of city life and immerse themselves in the beauty of nature.

featured_reviews.review_id: The place holds a very special place for the followers of Islam. It is called 'Poa Mecca' because it signifies one 'poa' or 1/4th part of the Holy Kaaba Sharif at Mecca, Saudi Arabia. People have a belief that their prayers are answered positively if they wish something here in Poa Mecca. Also, the 3 km stretch of road from the Poa Mecca Gate at the main road (SH-02) to the shrine is very beautiful, scenic and peaceful, covered with tall green trees. A well-built parking space has been provided by the authorities of Assam Tourism for the convenience of the visitors/devotees. Moreover, there are numerous shops near the entrance from where people can buy agarbatti (incense sticks), ittar/attar or other showpieces for homes.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Poa Mecca Dargah Sarif, also known as Hazarat Shah Sultan Giyasuddin R.A, is a famous Sufi shrine located in Hajo, Assam, India. It is considered to be one of the holiest places in Assam and is visited by both Muslims and Hindus.
The dargah is dedicated to Hazarat Shah Sultan Giyasuddin, a renowned Sufi saint who was born in Baghdad and later settled in Hajo. He is believed to have performed several miracles during his lifetime and is highly revered by the local population.The shrine attracts a large number of devotees, especially during the annual Urs festival, which commemorates the death anniversary of Hazarat Shah Sultan Giyasuddin. During this time, people from various parts of the country come to seek blessings and offer prayers at the dargah.Poa Mecca Dargah Sarif is known for its architectural beauty, with intricate carvings and designs adorning the walls and domes of the shrine. It serves as a symbol of religious harmony, as people from different faiths come together to pay their respects and seek spiritual solace.
Overall, Poa Mecca Dargah Sarif in Hajo, Assam, holds great religious and cultural significance and is a significant pilgrimage site for many devotees.
